
[1]naturalize

   NATURALIZE, v.t. [from natural, nature.]

   1. To confer on an alien the rights and privileges of a native subject
   or citizen; to adopt foreigners into a nation or state, and place them
   in the condition of natural born subjects.

   2. To make natural; to render easy and familiar by custom and habit;
   as, custom naturalizes labor or study.

   3. To adapt; to make suitable; to acclimate; as, to naturalize one to a
   climate.

   4. To receive or adopt as native, natural or vernacular; to make our
   own; as, to naturalize foreign words.

   5. To accustom; to habituate; as, to naturalize the vine to a cold
   climate.
